The paper involves Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Deep Learning models for Chess evaluation, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves training a Chess engine using Deep Learning models, which could fall under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing vast commentary datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV) if the commentary includes visual elements. Lastly, the paper involves sentiment analysis, which could fall under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) if the analysis is used to retrieve relevant information.
